"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-missouri-all-things-mizzou-former-missouri-swimmer-wins-bronze-at-olympics-the-buzz-august-5-2024-01j4g4f47sbw\", \"text\": \"Missouri Tiger alumni just keeps winning at the 2024 Paris Olympics, this time coming from swimmer Clement Secchi.  The 24-year-old won a bronze medal for France in the 4x100 Medlay Relay on Sunday, thanks to his excellent performance the third leg of the relay on Saturday's preliminary round. France finished with the best first heat time and best time overall (three minutes, 31.36 seconds).  Secchi had quite the resume at Missouri in just one season, becoming a three-time honorable mention All-America honoree and placing in the top five all-time in the 100m back, 100m fly, 200, back and 200m fly. Now, he is winning on a world stage.  Congrats, Clement! A bronze medal for the former Tiger!#MIZ| \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0090\\u00af |#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/PdiHtykxAJ  WATCH: Luther Burden (@lutherburden3) brought the ENERGY to Sunday's practice\\u00e2\\u009a\\u00a1\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f#Mizzou's star wide receiver led the team through Tiger Jacks this afternoon\\u00e2\\u00ac\\u0087\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f@NathalieABC17@ABC17Newspic.twitter.com/CvW8SfO3yZ  WATCH:#Mizzoufreshman Williams Nwaneri (@NwaneriWilliams) has earned his number on the first week of fall camp\\u00e2\\u00ac\\u0087\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008fThe Tigers got some great recent history with defensive players wearing No. 6\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u0080@NathalieABC17@ABC17Newspic.twitter.com/daN5LBCeV0  24 days.  Key Notes from Eli Drinkwitz After Week 1 of Missouri's Fall PracticesNotes and Observations from Practice 5 of Missouri Football's Fall Camp2024 Missouri Tigers Position Preview: Safeties2024 Missouri Tigers Position Preview: Cornerbacks  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Chase Gemes is a journalism student at the University of Missouri, and has served as sports editor for its student newspaper, The Manea